# 🎓 Advanced Student Management System (GUI)

A fully‑featured **Swing‑based desktop application** for managing students, courses, enrollments, grades, attendance, and generating reports. Data is persisted locally using Java serialization.

## ✨ Features

### 🧑 Student Management
- Add, update, delete students (ID, name, age)
- Search students by any field
- Real‑time table filtering

### 📚 Course Management
- Add/delete courses (code, name, credits – 1–6)
- Prevent deletion of courses with existing enrollments (with warning)

### 📋 Enrollment
- Enroll students in courses
- Withdraw students from courses
- Auto‑updates related grades and attendance

### 🎯 Grading
- Assign letter grades (A, B, C, D, F) or numeric (0‑100)
- Automatic GPA calculation (weighted by credits)
- Grade table with GPA value column

### 📅 Attendance
- Mark attendance percentage (0–100%) per student per course
- Slider + text field for easy input

### 📊 Reports
- **Student report** – courses enrolled, average GPA
- **Course report** – enrollment count, average grade
- **GPA report** – ranked list with academic standing (Dean's List, Probation, etc.)
- **Export all reports to CSV** (saved in `data/` folder)

### 💾 Data Persistence
- Automatic save on exit
- Data stored in `data/` folder as `.dat` files (Java serialization)
- Loads previous state on startup

### 🎨 User Interface
- Tabbed layout (6 tabs)
- System Look & Feel
- Responsive tables with sorting
- Input validation and error dialogs

## 🛠️ Requirements

- **Java JDK 11 or higher** (Swing is included)

## 📁 Project Structure
student-management-gui/
├── src/
│ └── studentManagementSystemGUI/
